        "value": 30,
        "description": "Typical for pulsed cleaning; 30 kHz recommended for Yttrium to enable fast processing while limiting heat accumulation in low-conductivity scenarios. Higher rates speed up but risk thermal damage. Source: Academic lit. in J. Phys. D: Appl. Phys. 44, 435301 (2011); trade-offs noted for rare earth metals."
