        "min": 0.1,
        "max": 1000,
        "unit": "ns",
        "value": 20,
        "description": "Nanosecond regime preferred for cost-effective cleaning of metals; 20 ns minimizes heat-affected zone (HAZ) on Yttrium due to its reactivity. Picosecond (ps) or femtosecond (fs) for ultra-precise but higher cost. Source: Laser physics in Appl. Phys. A 101, 147 (2010); avoids plasma shielding issues at 1064 nm."
      },
