        "min": 10,
        "max": 5000,
        "unit": "mm/s",
        "value": 2000,
        "description": "Effective for contaminant removal without excessive heat buildup; slower for heavy contamination (e.g., oxides), faster for light. Recommended 2000 mm/s balances efficiency and safety for Yttrium's thermal conductivity (17 W/m·K). Source: Industry standards from Laserax manuals; Opt. Lasers Eng. 47, 1069 (2009) for metal surfaces."
      },
